# Tracking Down a Thief – SQL Mystery Analysis

This project demonstrates SQL-based analysis by solving a fictional mystery using relational data. The goal was to identify the suspect behind the theft of the rare Cotton Candy Poodle by combining clues across multiple tables.

The investigation uses SQL joins, filtering, pattern matching, and aggregation to narrow down suspects based on location data, vehicle details, associate relationships, and alibi statements.

---

## Objective

The primary goals of this analysis were to:

- Identify suspects present at the crime scene
- Investigate suspect relationships and associates
- Match suspects to the getaway vehicle
- Analyze suspicious alibi statements
- Compare alibi locations with actual phone location data
- Combine all clue-based results to identify the final suspect

---

## Mystery Questions

- Which suspects were in Carnival City at the exact time of the crime?
- Which suspects have associates who are both friends and specialists?
- Which suspects own a minivan with a license plate ending in D0G?
- Which suspects have alibis containing the words dog, cotton, or candy?
- Which suspects have alibi locations that do not match their phone data?
- Which suspect appears in all result sets?

